 public service and research activities We are an internationally recognized center for the interdisciplinary study of disability engaged service across the spectrum of disability  including advocacy  culture  education  health promotion  history  policy and technology Institute on Disability and Human Development designated University Center for Excellence in Developmental Disabilities Education  Research and Service  n IDHD is a national leader in interdisciplinary academic training  community service  research and information dissemination all related to people with disabilities  n                    Find out more about IDHD n                  n nRead our           annual report n Our areas of research  scholarship and expertise Assistive Technology Autism Children  Youth and Families Community Living Cultural Competency Disability and Sexuality Disability Arts and Culture Disability Policy Entrepreneurship and Employment Health Disparities Health Promotion Intellectual and Developmental Disabilities Participation Among People with Disabilities Qualitative Research Rights and Advocacy Social Justice Meet our faculty and staff and connect with our programs n Meet our faculty and staff and connect with our programs Academic Programs  nRequest information n Request information Minor in Disability and Human Development Apply BS in Disability and Human Development Apply MS in Disability and Human Development Apply PhD in Disability Studies Apply Disability Ethics Certificate Apply Assistive Technology Certificate Apply What sets us apart Award winning faculty Sarah Parker Harris  Carrie Sandahl and Rooshey Hasnain receive AHS College Awards  and Aly Patsavas receives a UIC Excalibur Award for Teaching Excellence  n                Learn more n             Empowering stakeholders Stevie Hopkins  co founder of  E Love  The Wheelchair Heart  delivered  "Embrace  Educate  Empower  Love Life" to the AHS class of      in his commencement address  n                View the vi